<subSubSection id="4AB82C99BDE9BE496827E675B0F91895" type="description">
<paragraph id="284EC21A8B86501DC808D83C980EACA4" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="75" pageId="4" pageNumber="74" type="mainText">
Perennial herbs. Rhizomes thickened, hypogaeous, with a tuft of leaves at apex. Radical leaf blade narrowly ovate or narrowly triangular, cordate, acute to short acuminate, 4-10 cm long, 2-6 cm wide, usually shallowly 5-lobed, irregularly incised and acutely toothed, upper surface long hirsute, green, lower surface hirsute and glandular pubescent on nerves, pale green, often with purplish tinge; petiole 3-15 cm long, densely short glandular hairy, often with long glandular hairs, with a pair of axillary stipules at base; stipules scarious, densely 
<pageBreakToken id="40B1EEB33B50AD1414F67227F7D28AB2" pageId="5" pageNumber="75" start="start">long</pageBreakToken>
hairy along margin. Flowering stems 20-40 cm tall, erect, densely glandular pubescent. Inflorescences racemes, many-flowered. Flowers April to May; pedicel ca. 2-3 mm long, minutely glandular. Calyx tube obconical, densely glandular pubescent, greenish; calyx lobes 5, triangular or depressed-triangular, acute, glabrous adaxially, sparsely glandular abaxially, ca. 0.9 mm long, spreading or often reflexed, greenish. Petals 5, 3-7-pinnatiparted, glandular dotted, 2.5-3 mm long, spreading or slightly reflexed, greenish; pinnae slender, spreading or slightly obliquely ascending. Stamens 5, alternate calyx lobes, adjacent to base of petals, ca. 0.8-1.1 mm long; anthers ovoid, cordate, 0.7-0.9 mm long at anthesis, yellow. Disc prominent, flat, greenish. Ovary inferior. Styles 2, erect, ca. 0.5 mm long; stigmas thickened, shallowly 2-5-lobed, yellowish green. Seeds oblong, ca. 1.1 mm long, scabrous, with narrow longitudinal areolae elevated slightly, without papillae, brownish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ADD30640D7752B18997DA8385C59796A" pageId="5" pageNumber="75" type="mainText">Chromosome number: 2n = 28 (Wakabayashi 1973).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
